SQL Learning Plan + Practice Exercises
Beginner Level
1. Introduction to Databases & SQL

Practice:
Explain what a database is.
Describe tables and rows with examples.

2. Basic SQL Queries

https://sqlitebrowser.org/dl/    Download from here

Exercise:
Write a query to select all columns from a table Employees.
Select only name and age columns.
Practice dataset: Create a simple Employees table.

3. Working with Columns

Exercise:
Use aliases to rename name as EmployeeName.
Use COUNT() to find number of employees.

4. Filtering Data

Exercise:
Find employees older than 30.
Find employees with names starting with 'A' using LIKE.

5. Aggregate Functions & Grouping

Exercise:
Group employees by department and count employees in each.
Find average salary per department.

Intermediate Level
6. Joins

Exercise:
Join Employees with Departments on department_id.
Use left join to find employees without a department.

7. Subqueries

Exercise:
Find employees who earn more than the average salary.
Find departments with more than 5 employees.

8. Set Operations

Exercise:
Combine two employee lists using UNION.
Find employees who are in list A but not in list B using EXCEPT.

9. Modifying Data

Exercise:
Insert a new employee.
Update salary for a specific employee.
Delete employees who left the company.

10. Creating and Managing Tables

Exercise:
Create a Projects table with appropriate columns.
Alter table to add a new column.

Advanced Level
11. Indexes and Performance

Exercise:
Create indexes on Employees(name).
Analyze query performance before and after.

12. Views

Exercise:
Create a view showing employee names and their department names.

13. Stored Procedures and Functions

Exercise:
Write a procedure to increase salary by 10%.
Create a function to calculate yearly bonus.

14. Transactions & Concurrency

Exercise:
Write a transaction to transfer funds between accounts.
Simulate concurrent transactions and observe locks.

15. Advanced SQL Features

Exercise:
Use window functions to rank employees by salary.
Write a recursive query to find hierarchical data.

What to Download to Practice SQL Locally
1. Database Systems

Choose one based on your OS and preference. All are free:

MySQL / MariaDB
Widely used, beginner-friendly
Download: https://dev.mysql.com/downloads/
MariaDB is a compatible fork: https://mariadb.org/download/

PostgreSQL
Powerful, feature-rich, great for advanced queries
Download: https://www.postgresql.org/download/

SQLite
Lightweight, no server needed, great for beginners
Download: https://sqlite.org/download.html

SQL Server Express (Windows only)
Free edition of MS SQL Server
Download: https://www.microsoft.com/en-us/sql-server/sql-server-downloads

2. SQL Clients / IDEs

To write and run SQL queries easily:
DBeaver (free, supports many DBs)
https://dbeaver.io/download/
MySQL Workbench (for MySQL)
https://dev.mysql.com/downloads/workbench/
pgAdmin (for PostgreSQL)
https://www.pgadmin.org/download/
DB Browser for SQLite
https://sqlitebrowser.org/dl/

